reviewText: Very entertaining film!  One of George Nader's best Jerry Cotton films he did, glad to have a copy of it!

Muredrers' Club Of Brooklyn was released in 1967. It starred George Nader as FBI agent Jerry Cotton, for the first time in color. A fine B-Film. The story has Jerry in pursuit of a gang of kidnappers who commit murder. Fans of George Nader will like this the most.
